I"5<p>Mary Caton Lingold is a doctoral candidate in English at Duke, where she is completing a dissertation on early Afro-Atlantic literature and music. She is co-editor of the web collection <a href="http://soundboxproject.com/">Provoke!: Digital Sound Studies</a>, and a book by the same name and under contract at Duke UP. Her article on music in Caribbean travel narratives is forthcoming in <em>Early American Literature.</em> She also directs the <a href="https://sonicdictionary.duke.edu/">Sonic Dictionary</a>, a crowdsourced database of audio recordings.</p>
